get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/measurements/engines
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 Group B - Engine oil + coolant temperature.

  Returns nested temperature blocks per engine. Surfaced as two
  numeric sensors: ``engine_oil_temperature_c`` and
  ``engine_coolant_temperature_c``. Both phantom-protected via
  ``_DATA_PRESENT_REQUIRED`` so EV-only vehicles and other brands
  stay clean.

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Engine Measurements sequence), independently parsed in
  ``seat_cupra.get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape (observed across PHEV Formentor + ICE Leon):
    {
      "engines": [
        {
          "type": "primary",
          "oilTemperature": {"valueInKelvin": 363.15},
          "coolantTemperature": {"valueInCelsius": 87.4}
        },
        ...
      ]
    }

  Firmware variance:
  - Some ship a flat dict instead of a list.
  - Some ship temperatures directly as bare floats (treated as
    Kelvin when above 200, Celsius otherwise).
  - Some skip the ``engines`` envelope entirely.

  The parser accepts all three shapes plus the nested
  ``valueInCelsius`` / ``valueInKelvin`` / ``value`` / ``temperature``
  variants on the temperature block itself.

  Soft-fails to ``{}`` on 401 / 403 / 404.
}
